# Figma-CLI-G — Full Code Review & Improvement Roadmap

> **Goal:** Connect to Figma fast using free AI models with clear logic, clear workflow, and build complex design systems + components fast and easy without hallucinations.

---

## 🔴 Critical Bugs Found (Connection Failures)

These are the **root causes** of why the AI couldn't connect to Figma in your [logs](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/logs/Connecting-logs.txt):

### Bug 1: `curl` used everywhere — doesn't exist on Windows
**Severity:** 🔴 BLOCKING — kills ALL connection logic on Windows

The codebase uses `curl` in **9 places** inside [src/index.js](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js) for daemon health checks, command execution, and connection validation. `curl` is a Unix tool — it does **not** exist on most Windows PowerShell/CMD environments natively.

| Line | Function | What breaks |
|------|----------|-------------|
| L46 | [isDaemonRunning()](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js#41-56) | Daemon health check fails silently → returns `false` |
| L288 | [figmaEvalSync()](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js#270-350) | All sync evaluations fail → commands don't execute |
| L303 | [figmaEvalSync()](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js#270-350) | Safe mode health fallback fails |
| L374 | [figmaUse('status')](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js#351-443) | Status check broken |
| L450 | [checkConnection()](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js#444-468) | Connection check always fails → "Not connected" |
| L475 | [checkConnectionSync()](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js#469-495) | Same as above, sync version |
| L485 | [checkConnectionSync()](file:///d:/Design/AI/Project-ongoing/Figma-CLI-G/figma-cli-g/src/index.js#469-495) | CDP direct check fails |
| L981 | connect `--safe` | Safe mode plugin health check fails |

**Fix:** Replace ALL `curl` calls with Node.js native `fetch()` (available since Node 18+) or `http.request()`.

### Bug 2: `/tmp/` hardcoded paths — Windows doesn't have `/tmp/`
**Severity:** 🔴 BLOCKING — crashes file-based eval fallback

| Line | What breaks |
|------|-------------|
| L283 | `figmaEvalSync` payload file writes to `/tmp/` |
| L315-316 | Fallback eval script + result files written to `/tmp/` |
| L2862 | Screenshot temp file |
| L3000, L3006 | URL analysis scripts |
| L3164 | Recreate URL scripts |
| L3416 | Remove-bg temp file |

**Fix:** Replace `/tmp/` with `os.tmpdir()` (already imported but not used for these paths).

### Bug 3: `sleep 0.3` Unix command in `startDaemon()`
**Severity:** 🟡 HIGH — daemon restart fails on Windows

Line 128: `execSync('sleep 0.3', { stdio: 'pipe' })` — `sleep` is a Unix command.

**Fix:** Use `Atomics.wait(new Int32Array(new SharedArrayBuffer(4)), 0, 0, 300)` or `setTimeout`.

### Bug 4: `lsof` used in `stopDaemon()`
**Severity:** 🟡 HIGH — daemon port cleanup fails on Windows

Line 161: `execSync('lsof -ti:${DAEMON_PORT} | xargs kill -9 ...')` — Unix only.

**Fix:** Use `netstat -ano | findstr :PORT` + `taskkill /PID` on Windows, wrapped in platform check.

### Bug 5: `rm -f` used in `figmaEvalSync()` fallback
**Severity:** 🟡 MEDIUM — temp file cleanup fails silently

Line 340, 345: `execSync('rm -f ${tempFile} ${resultFile}')` — Unix only.

**Fix:** Use `fs.unlinkSync()` (already imported).

### Bug 6: Daemon port `EADDRINUSE` crash
**Severity:** 🟡 HIGH — logs show daemon crashes when port 3456 is occupied

The daemon in `src/daemon.js` line 406 calls `httpServer.listen()` without handling `EADDRINUSE`. If a previous daemon didn't shut down cleanly, the new one crashes immediately.

**Fix:** Add port-in-use detection + auto-kill previous process before binding.

### Bug 7: `taskkill /F /PID` fails from PowerShell
**Severity:** 🟡 HIGH — AI agent literally couldn't kill processes (visible in logs)

The logs show `ERROR: Invalid argument/option - 'F:/'` repeated 6+ times. This happens because PowerShell interprets `/F` as a path. The code at line 201 uses `taskkill /IM Figma.exe /F` which works, but AI agents calling `taskkill /F /PID` from PowerShell fail.

**Fix:** Use `Stop-Process -Id PID -Force` for PowerShell, or wrap in `cmd /c "taskkill /F /PID X"`.

